Appeals to all Nigerians to be law abiding... The Federal Government has appeal to Law Enforcement Agencies to deploy tact and caution in the course of enforcing the rules, even, in the face of provocation.  The Chairman of the Presidential Task Force Mr. Boss Mustapha who said this during Friday's briefing similarly appealed to all Nigerians to be law abiding. He noted that in recognition of the danger to which front-line health workers are exposed to, government is working with other stakeholders to structure medical and life insurance cover for their protection.  Fielding questions on the projected global food crisis, Mr Mustapha said the Government is taking steps to boost Agricultural productions in order to address food crisis as the nation fights Coronavirus.  Also speaking on the fight against Coronavirus, Dr Chikwe Ihekweazu, Director General of Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC), says Nigeria now has eight laboratories as the Bio-Security Centre in Lagos is added to the seven existing laboratories to conduct sample tests for the Coronavirus (Covid-19) and the agency is planning to review its testing strategies to expand its testing capacity.  Dr Chikwe noted that to date about 6,700 contacts are being traced with about 4,000 persons tested.